lines.text: used to ride up on the hill
and my heart jumped eve-ry ledge
until one bright morn-ing when i woke
i heard bells, girl she gent-ly spoke and said
'choice my man's to breath or choke
so go die, or learn to hope'
un-der the fire and the rain
you wake up on yo-ur own
some-times the world just hits your chin
and some-times sha-dows haunt your back
and some-times i feel so flat
like some rare ea-gle on the wind
well it turns and life comes burst-ing in
and the earth you thought would beat you down
lifts up and lights your ground
un-der the fire and the rain
you wake up on yo-ur own
un-der the fire and the rain
you wake up on yo-ur own
un-der the fire and the rain
you wake up on your own
